




1- first of all we have to create a cluster

2- Create a role in IAM console

	-select EKS service
	-choose EKS cluster

3- Create a VPC in the network part with "Cloudformation"





-------------------------------------------------------------




1- goto "compute" section and "add a node group"


2- create another role for "ELS worker policy"


3- then create worker nodes (t3.micro)




**** it creates EC2 instances




-------------------------------------------------------------




1- install AWS CLI on the local machine

2- goto AWS account security credential  --->   Create a new access-key  (access-key,secret-key)

3- run this commands to add AWS on your machine:

	$ aws configure

4- update kubectl command for connect to your AWS instead of minikube:

	$ aws eks --region us-east-2 update-kubeconfig --name kub-dep-demo




-------------------------------------------------------------




now we can deploy with kubectl command




